name: N'fa
description: '''N'fa''' (born '''N'fa Deynde Jo Jo Forster-Jones'''; also known as '''N'fa Jones''', 21 March 1979) is a British-born [[African Australian]] [[Hip hop music|hip hop]] recording artist. He was born in [[London]], but raised in [[Perth, Western Australia]], and is best known as the frontman for [[1200 Techniques]]. Forster-Jones was a nationally ranked 110m hurdler and placed third at the 2001 and 2002 Australian Championships, and fourth in the 2000 Olympic trials. His personal best recorded time was 14.08s (wind: +1.8) set in Brisbane on 25 March 2001, though clocked 13.91 "unofficial" in Auckland's trans-Tasman test meet in 2001.
